## Worked Example

Updating `[3,6]` uses $f(i)=i-2$. It contributes values 1, 2, 3, 4. On node `[4,5]`, the sum change is $(4+5)-2\cdot2=5$, matching $2+3$.

## Takeaway

Progression updates become simple lazy propagation when rewritten as a polynomial in the global index and summed in closed form over a node.

### Related problems

Range Updates and Sums composes assignment and constant addition. Increasing Array Queries uses lazy range assignment for an offline monotone frontier.

