With reserved points including $(1,1)$ and free point $(1,3)$, the ordinary southwest sweep inserts $(1,1)$ before the query. It returns maximum sum 2, so the distance candidate is $(1+3)-2=2$, which is the final nearest distance.

## Takeaway

Offline sorting plus a Fenwick tree is a standard engine for two dimensional dominance optimization, not only for counting.

