## Worked Example

In permutation `[2,3,1]`, values 2 and 3 conflict: 2 appears first, $2<3$, and unread value 1 is smaller than 2. They must use different stacks, after which 1 may share either compatible stack.

## Takeaway

Stack-sortability constraints often appear as forbidden permutation patterns. Turn pairwise conflicts into graph coloring, then compress interval-shaped neighborhoods with ordered sets and parity DSU.

### Related problems

Giant Pizza also reduces a binary assignment to consistency constraints, using SCC rather than parity DSU.

